<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2444] Remove checkAllColumnFamilies on startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2444</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve ran into many times where we do not want compaction to run right away against CFs when booting up a node. If the node needs to compact, it will do so at the first flush&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12503814">CASSANDRA-2444</key>
            <summary>Remove checkAllColumnFamilies on startup</summary>
