                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13022981" author="stuhood" created="Thu, 21 Apr 2011 23:30:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rather than adding an option for this, I think we should remove the check entirely. If the node needs to compact, it will do so at the first flush, which is more likely to be staggered across the cluster (and if this flush is forced by commitlogs, then AOK).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023112" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 04:47:36 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rather than adding an option for this, I think we should remove the check entirely. If the node needs to compact, it will do so at the first flush&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023459" author="hudson" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 23:31:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.8 #35 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.8/35/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.8/35/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Remove checking all column families on startup for compaction candidates&lt;br/&gt;
